{
  "text": "Finally, we compare our results with those obtained from the robust block-level precoding scheme proposed in [CITATION_1] , referred to as \"robust BLP,\" which solves a convex semidefinite programming (SDP) to minimize the average transmit power for a given target SINR \u03b3. It is important to note that the robust BLP approach is barely feasible for large \u03b3 and \u03be 2 as well as small values of \u03c5 (as we will show in Fig. 15 ). Therefore, in what follows, we present the results for some limited scenarios with sufficiently small \u03b3 and \u03be 2 and large enough \u03c5. Furthermore, we average the results obtained form the robust BLP scheme only over those realizations for which the SDP optimization problem in [CITATION_2] is feasible.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "5876787",
    "[CITATION_2]": "5876787"
